ZH: 昨天晚上公司有个紧急项目，我不得不熬夜加班。
EN: Last night my company had an urgent project, so I had to work overtime and pull an all-nighter.

ZH: 熬夜对身体不好，容易导致各种健康问题。
EN: Staying up all night is bad for your health and can lead to various health issues.

ZH: 我熬夜写论文，终于在凌晨完成了。
EN: I stayed up all night writing my paper and finally finished it in the early morning.

ZH: 他常常熬夜玩游戏，最后弄得身体很虚弱。
EN: He often stays up late playing games, and it has left him very weak.

ZH: 考试前我总是习惯熬夜复习。
EN: I always stay up late to review before exams.

ZH: 熬夜看电影是我的最爱，即使第二天上班要迟到也值得。
EN: Staying up all night to watch movies is my favorite thing to do, even if it means being late for work the next day.

ZH: 她不得不熬夜工作，以确保这个项目按时完成。
EN: She had to stay up all night working to make sure the project was completed on time.

ZH: 他面临着重要考试，所以他决定熬夜复习。
EN: He has an important exam coming up, so he has decided to stay up all night to study.

ZH: 熬夜后第二天早上总是感觉很疲倦。
EN: I always feel very tired the next morning after staying up all night.

ZH: 熬夜工作对我们的身体和心理健康都有很大影响。
EN: Staying up all night working has a great impact on both our physical and mental health.

ZH: 在上大学的时候，我常常熬夜写作业。
EN: When I was in college, I often stayed up all night doing homework.

ZH: 她为了参加比赛，不得不熬夜练习。
EN: She had to stay up all night practicing for the competition.

ZH: 熬夜会导致皮肤变差，所以我尽量避免。
EN: Staying up all night can make your skin worse, so I try to avoid it as much as possible.

ZH: 我昨晚熬夜看电视剧，结果一整天都没精神。
EN: I stayed up all night watching a TV series last night, and as a result, I felt lethargic all day.

ZH: 看到他们为了完成任务熬夜的样子，我觉得心疼。
EN: Seeing them staying up all night to complete the task, I felt sorry for them.

ZH: 熬夜对身体的伤害是不可逆转的，所以要尽量避免。
EN: The damage to the body caused by staying up all night is irreversible, so it is best to avoid it as much as possible.

ZH: 我们每个人都不得不偶尔熬夜，但不能经常。
EN: We all have to stay up all night occasionally, but it should not be a regular occurrence.

ZH: 为了赶工程进度，他们不得不连续几天熬夜。
EN: In order to meet the project deadline, they had to stay up all night for several days in a row.

ZH: 熬夜看书虽然累，但也是一种享受。
EN: Staying up all night reading books is tiring, but it is also a kind of enjoyment.

ZH: 尽管熬夜不好，但在某些特殊情况下是不可避免的。
EN: Although staying up all night is not good, it is unavoidable in certain special circumstances.
